[1] Mali: UN mission scraps clinic contract
Date: Sun 16 Nov 2014
Source: Reuters [edited]
http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/11/16/us-health-ebola-mali-idUSKCN0J00C120141116


The United Nations mission in Mali has canceled plans to renew a contract with a private clinic providing care to its peacekeepers after a case of Ebola was missed and spread from there... The UN mission in Mali, whose peacekeepers are helping to protect the nation against Islamist rebels, reversed on Sat [15 Nov 2014] a decision taken earlier in the week to renew the contract with the Pasteur Clinic in Bamako to care for sick or injured troops. A UN spokesman said the decision was taken "due to prevailing circumstances," but gave no further details.

[byline: David Lewis]

