[2] Guinea-Bissau reopens borders with Ebola-stricken Guinea
Date: 15 Nov 2014
Source: StarAfrica (APA) [edited]
http://en.starafrica.com/news/gbissau-reopens-borders-with-ebola-stricken-guinea.html


Guinea Bissau's general director of prevention and health promotion Nicholas Almeida announced on Sat [15 Nov 2014] the reopening of borders with Ebola-hit Guinea to facilitate trade between the 2 countries.

"We will continue to reinforce the preventive measures against the deadly Ebola virus," Mr Almeida said, pointing out that the emergency plan would be still in force despite the lack of means to fully put it in place. Guinea Bissau is currently unable to afford an epidemiological monitoring, he said, recalling a summit which brought together heads of states and governments from the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS), which recommended the reopening of the borders. The health expert said that some 40 entry points have been identified as requiring great attention.

"Screening units are set up in the hospital Simoes Mendes in Bissau and across the region," Almeida said, while pointing to the already launched emergency plans, including radio sensitization campaigns and training sessions for health workers.

